    <p class="text-gray-700">The biggest mistake is choosing Zinfandels based solely on high alcohol content (16%+), assuming it equals quality—these often taste hot and unbalanced. Many buyers also confuse White Zinfandel with red Zinfandel, or purchase very cheap bottles expecting premium quality. Always check the vintage date, as Zinfandel doesn't improve significantly with age beyond 8-10 years for most bottlings.</p>
